  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Screen Reader Behavior</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Announced as "description list" with item count</li>
      <li>Terms (<code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>) announced as labels or keys</li>
      <li>Descriptions (<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code>) announced as associated values</li>
      <li>Users can navigate between term-description groups</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Use for genuine term-description relationships</li>
      <li>Keep terms concise and descriptive</li>
      <li>Ensure descriptions provide meaningful information</li>
      <li>Maintain logical grouping of <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> pairs</li>
      <li>Consider using <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> to group term-description pairs for styling (HTML5 allows this)</li>
    </ul>

